 Port Elizabeth - Police in Motherwell have appealed to the public for assistance with information that can assist them in locating a missing teenager. "The 13-year-old Mbasa Ngindo have been reported missing from her home in Ranisi Street, NU8, Motherwell, since Monday morning," described police spokesperson, Captain Andre Beetge. "This follows after she was last seen watching television in the lounge on Sunday, at about 22:00, when her parents went to sleep. "The next morning (on Monday) at about 05:00, the parents discovered that she was no longer in the house." Capt Beetge said that it is also suspected that the girl packed a small bag of clothing. "A missing persons report was opened at Motherwell SAPS and any person that could assist police in locating the girl can contact Captain Monica Ndabankulu at 083 759 7551." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 